##What can Wuhan learn from the experience of SARS?

Hey, guys

Function description, here is the "First Finance" magazine (predecessor "first finance weekly") readers club, we discover wonderful business value for you, also invited you to explore the bright business world.

Financial Reporter | Xiaohua Ma

First financial's flagship APP

So far, in the fight against the outbreak of tension in the campaign, the eye of the storm in Wuhan inevitably some hands and feet.

On the one hand, medical supplies are in short supply, masks, protective clothing, goggles of the information on the network for help spread; on the other hand, medical resources are in short supply, the front-line staff exhausted, coupled with hospital beds... . As a result, suspected patients can not be confirmed, no access to hospital began to appear, more than one member of a family with suspected symptoms is not a small number.

Some people blame Wuhan for losing ground, but more people pray for Wuhan at the same time, more in the advice, for the hero of the city to cheer. Experience and a bold response can help a city under pressure to quickly find a solution.

China's experience in successfully fighting SARS should not be forgotten.

When the first finance reporter interviewed two medical personnel who had been in the first-line treatment of SARS, they shared the view that the hardware of medical institutions and the auxiliary conditions of society at the time when SARS was raging in Beijing in 2003 were far inferior to those of today, also experienced the initial panic and difficult admission. The key to the victory was that Beijing quickly found a solution to bring medical institutions into order.

For now, the conclusion is that Wuhan Needs Unified Coordination and management, the government, health administration departments, medical institutions must have a unified pace and implementation, in order to play a stronger role.

Territorial Management

"when SARS came, China was really caught off guard, and Beijing was a hard-hit area. But the problem was quickly solved,"Han Zhengzheng, director of Desheng Community Health Center in Beijing, told China Business News.

In 2003, Han Zhengzheng was deputy director of Beijing Dewai Hospital, the designated SARS hospital in Xicheng District, Beijing, which is now renamed Desheng Community Health Center.

Han said that at that time, the government had a directive requiring local management, each district to set up designated hospitals to treat patients in the region, and to support designated hospitals with all the medical resources and supplies in the region. The program quickly solved the problem of difficult admission of patients in the region.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Localized management, each district set up fixed-point hospital is the experience left by SARS.

"This management method not only makes it easier for patients to be treated nearby, but also allows the deployment of medical resources. We didn't have outside medical teams at the time. We relied on district-wide medical resources. You work in teams of 10, you work on the front lines for two weeks, and then you assemble a second team to replace the first team. The first echelons were concentrated in a hotel in Changping District, isolated for two weeks and then replaced,"Han said, medical staff can not be in the front line, otherwise physical strength and immunity will decline, more prone to medical infections.

This kind of relay race played a very important role at the time. It is also because of the rational use of medical forces, but also to protect the strength of this team in combat.

In addition, the use of medical supplies was orderly, Han said. "there was no such network, only phone calls or emails. We called the Xicheng District Health Bureau every day to tell them how much medical supplies we needed, and the health bureau would send a car. "

Han Zhengzheng said that the management of medical materials also needs to be planned, and the distribution also needs to be scientific, especially in dividing and opening boxes. Instead of putting a bunch of things together and sending them to a hospital, the hospital takes what it needs, and get the rest back. As long as there is open box, there is pollution, so these materials will no longer have a medical institution to accept.

This kind of territorial management not only solves the problem of manpower and material resources in an orderly way, but also does well the medical management of the public in this area.

"We have 150 medical personnel, 100 of whom are on the front line of diagnosis and treatment, and the remaining 50 medical personnel who are in charge of medical observation for the whole community, guiding the residents in the community on how to sterilize and how to observe symptoms such as fever, as well as carrying out epidemiological investigations, " said Han.

This kind of personal guidance of medical staff, not only brought professional prevention and control knowledge, more importantly, to calm the hearts of panic.

The effective localization management, after SARS, was written in the August 2004 revision "the Infectious Disease Prevention Law" .

Effective isolation + classified management

Orderly prevention and control, but also inseparable from the classification of management.

"patients with a clear diagnosis are admitted to hospital in time and treated centrally. Those who need medical observation are concentrated in hotels, " said Han.

At the time, Han said, the hospital commandeered two hotels, the then October building and Changping District's hotel, as Sentinel medical observation points. This sort of management, for the control of the epidemic has played a very important role, not only to be able to find patients in time, also do not need to use too much medical resources.

It was under such unified management that Beijing soon brought SARS under control.

In fact, Wuhan as early as January 24, also proposed a hierarchical classification of the work arrangements.

On the same day, Wuhan held a video scheduling meeting on the implementation of classified screening work. The meeting put forward the idea of entering a "wartime" state in an all-round way. The system of classified medical treatment should be implemented to ensure that patients with fever receive timely treatment.

Wuhan's approach is to be responsible for the community, a comprehensive screening of fever patients in their jurisdiction, and sent to the Community Health Service Center for screening, classification, to avoid the disorder of patient flow, reduce cross-infection in the hospital.

At the same time, the districts have fully implemented the territorial responsibility system, with the main leaders acting as the first responsible persons, immediately identifying isolated observation sites and transporting special vehicles for patients, implementing the Community Health Service Centres and medical forces, and identifying suspected patients, timely referral to the fever clinic and immediate referral to the designated medical point for treatment; enhanced sharing of medical resources between sectors to ensure unconditional admission of all suspected patients.

All streets and communities shall be jointly controlled, mass controlled, mass controlled, and mass controlled. Fever patients within their jurisdiction shall be checked and registered with full coverage and followed throughout. Community gathering activities shall be cancelled in time to urge the masses not to hold family gatherings and to reduce going out.

Wuhan Health Commission is required to send doctors to each district as soon as possible to provide necessary support to the community.

But the reality after the event shows that such a classification of medical treatment system, and did not achieve the ideal goal. Many patients have been isolated in the community, unable to get timely treatment. Wuhan Doctors on social media urged: Suspected Cases can not be confirmed, they can not be admitted to hospital treatment, a large number of suspected patients outside the hospital, the source of infection can not be effectively controlled. Only by isolating all suspected patients can the source of infection be most effectively controlled and the route of transmission cut off. At the same time, the hospital's other departments can only function properly if suspected patients are all quarantined.

Miao Xiaohui, a former deputy director of the Second Military Medical University who helped treat SARS, said strong command and coordination were needed to effectively control order at the scene.

Things are definitely changing.

On February 2, the pneumonia control and Prevention Headquarters of the Wuhan COVID-19 requested that all urban districts complete the centralized admission of confirmed patients and the centralized isolation of suspected patients by 12 o'clock on February 2, can Not rule out the fever patients and close contacts of the confirmed patients concentrated isolation observation, additional personnel "clear moon knot. ".

According to the requirements of the prevention and control headquarters, "four categories of personnel" classified centralized admission and isolation. Patients who have been diagnosed must be admitted to a centralized facility. Serious patients must be sent to the designated hospital for treatment, mild patients can not all enter the designated hospital for treatment, other hospitals or hotels must be requisitioned as a temporary treatment area, centralized treatment.

The command requested that the "four categories of personnel" be treated and quarantined separately, and arranged for centralized treatment and quarantine points of medical personnel and logistical support.

Centralized admission, centralized isolation, centralized isolation observation, Wuhan will get rid of the previous confusion and panic, into an orderly track.

Efficient use of resources

Once the management is unified and the medical resources are used effectively, the problems of material shortage and medical force shortage that Perplex Wuhan will also be solved.

For example, judging by the number of paramedics. Miao Xiaohui explained to CBN that there is a very important concept of patient-to-patient ratio, and different types of patients have different medical-to-patient ratios.

"For patients under treatment, the ratio of medical staff plus support staff to patients is 1.5-2:1; for patients under observation in hospitals, the need for medical care is halved; for medical observation in hotels, the ratio of medical observation staff to observed staff is 1:15-20. And one in 50 of those in charge of medical observation will do."

As of 2400 hours on 1 February 2020, a total of 4109 cases of COVID-19 pneumonia have been reported in Wuhan. If the above scale top grid (2:1) is used and all 4,109 patients fall into the first category, 8,218 paramedics and support staff may be required. Therefore, at present, all over the country to go to Wuhan aid medical team's strength, has greatly eased the pressure of Wuhan Medical Staff.

On January 24, the first medical teams from Shanghai and Guangdong arrived in Wuhan. Nearly 6,000 medical teams from all over the country will support the prevention and treatment of the epidemic in Wuhan, Hubei Province, as of the evening of January 28, Jiao Yahui, deputy director of the medical and Health Administration Bureau of the National Health and Health Commission, said at a news conference on January 28.

On February 2, another 1,400 medics flew to Wuhan.

So, is there pressure on the number of beds?

According to information released by the Wuhan Municipal Government, Wuhan has set up 61 fever clinics in the city, the full implementation of 24-hour consultations. On the basis of the two hospitals of Jinyintan Hospital and Lung Hospital, 24 general hospitals have been requisitioned in three batches and have been temporarily transformed into special hospitals for patients with fever. The Wuhan Government expects to provide more than 13,000 beds by February 5.

On February 2, Wuhan announced the use of beds in 23 designated hospitals in the city: 6,754 beds have been opened and 6,808 beds have actually been used.

February 2 morning, Wuhan Huoshenshan Hospital delivery ceremony. The 33,900 square meter Gross leasable area in Wuhan, which has a capacity of 1,000 beds, will officially admit patients with COVID-19 infection on March 3, according to the report, referring to the construction of Beijing Xiaotangshan Hospital during SARS in 2003.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Vulcan Mountain Hospital has a capacity of 1,000 beds.

At the same time, the first financial statistics found that 9 designated hospitals (City Fifth Hospital, City Third Hospital, Union Hospital, Provincial People's Hospital, etc.) , a total of 12,476 beds.

"There are plenty of medical resources in Wuhan, but it's just a question of how to use them. There are a lot of third-class hospitals with 1,000 beds. Now a lot of patients are coming in, waiting for a new hospital? [ to ] vacate the existing hospital! " Miao said.

Compared with the number of confirmed cases, Wuhan Medical Care, beds and other medical resources pressure has been greatly eased. But the problem now is that the number of people who will remain in the hospital remains uncertain, and it is difficult to predict how many more people will be infected in the future. In addition, the number of patients who were previously ill and could not be admitted to hospital and had to be quarantined at home is not yet known, the challenges still lie ahead.

According to the Wuhan government, there will be no more attendance figures from January 29, but according to first financial, the 6,808 beds it has claimed and the total number of confirmed cases is 4,109, more than 2,000 people watched. According to official statistics on January 28, there are 12,263 outpatient clinics in Wuhan every day, and it is impossible to predict how many more people will be infected in the future. According to the 2.2 infection index calculated by Takatomi et Al.'s model, there are 4,109 confirmed cases, there could be 9,039 infections.

But as Wuhan redeploys, such as the expropriation of hotels, and so on, the picture of all patients flocking to hospitals will improve. At the same time, simplifying and shortening the screening process can avoid multiple rounds of suspected cases to the hospital causing more cross-infection, by simplifying the diagnosis of triage procedures, can avoid mild cases, home isolation observers delay into serious illness. When the overall allocation of medical resources began to become orderly, Wuhan will gradually get on the right track.
